&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About Vercel:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Vercel is the agentic infrastructure company. We free people and agents to ship what’s next.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;For more than a decade, Vercel has shaped how the web is built. As the team behind Next.js, v0, and AI SDK, we create products that help builders move from idea to production with speed, security, and exceptional developer experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Now, software is entering a new era, and the next generation of products will not just be used by people. They will be built, extended, and operated by agents.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;We are building the platform for that future, trusted by companies like&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;OpenAI, PayPal, Ramp, Supreme, and millions of developers worldwide&lt;/strong&gt;. Whether you’re building our products, supporting our customers, growing our community, or shaping our story, you’ll help define what comes next.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About the role:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Software Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to join the &lt;strong&gt;Agent Stack&lt;/strong&gt; team and help build eve — Vercel&#39;s framework for building production-ready AI agents. Eve is to agents what Next.js is to web apps: an opinionated, batteries-included framework that lets developers write only what&#39;s unique about their agent and have the platform handle the rest. You will design and implement core framework primitives, contribute to eve&#39;s runtime (built on Vercel Workflows, AI SDK, and Sandbox), and help shape the developer experience for the next generation of AI-native applications. You will report to the &lt;strong&gt;Director of Vercel&#39;s Agent Stack&lt;/strong&gt; and will be located &lt;strong&gt;onsite in New York City&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re based within a pre-determined commuting distance of one of our offices (SF, NY, London, or Berlin), the role includes in-office anchor days on Monday, Tuesday, and Friday, even if the role is listed as remote. For location-specific details, please connect with our recruiting team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you will do:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and ship core Eve framework features — the file-system conventions, compiler, and runtime that turn an agent directory into a durable, production-ready agent on Vercel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain integrations across Eve&#39;s channel layer (Slack, Web Chat, WhatsApp, API, Cron, and more) and connections layer (Vercel Connect / MCP endpoints).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the AI SDK, Workflows, and Sandbox teams to ensure Eve&#39;s primitives compose seamlessly on the Vercel platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive DX quality — CLI ergonomics, error messages, docs, and examples — so TypeScript/Next.js developers can ship their first agent in minutes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to Eve&#39;s evaluation and observability story: test suites, scoring rubrics, and deployment-time evals that make agents production-safe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with early customers and internal teams to gather feedback, diagnose agent reliability issues, and iterate rapidly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About you:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of production TypeScript/JavaScript experience; comfortable owning complex, stateful systems end to end.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of distributed systems concepts — durable execution, checkpointing, async workflows, and failure recovery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building or operating developer tooling, frameworks, or SDKs used by external developers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with LLM APIs and agent orchestration patterns (tool calling, multi-agent delegation, human-in-the-loop flows).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of shipping high-quality open-source or customer-facing APIs and caring deeply about API design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The New York, NY base pay range for this role is $208,000-$312,000. Actual salary will be based on job-related skills, experience, and location. Compensation outside of San Francisco may be adjusted based on employee location. The total compensation package may include benefits, equity-based compensation, and eligibility for a company bonus or variable pay program depending on the role. Your recruiter can share more details during the hiring process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vercel is committed to fostering and empowering an inclusive community within our organization. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, citizenship, age, marital status, veteran status, disability status, or any other characteristic protected by law. Vercel encourages everyone to apply for our available positions, even if they don&#39;t necessarily check every box on the job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
